New Urban Center Construction Begins in Shenzhen
SHENZHEN , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- Construction of the six key projects for the new city center in the city of Shenzhen , the well-known special economic zone in south China neighboring Hong Kong , got underway today .
These projects , at a cost of over 12 billion yuan ( about 1.44 billion U.S. dollars ) , include the building of a metro-station , a TV center , a cultural center , a library and two recreational centers .
The new city center will cover 413 hectares , will integrate administration facilities with cultural , information and commercial activities , and will be able to accommodate 77,000 people .
